credit portfolio
the following table presents jpmorgan chases credit portfolio as of december31, 2009
and 2008. total credit exposure at december31, 2009, decreased by $322.6billion from december31,
2008, reflecting decreases of $170.5billion in the wholesale portfolio and $152.1billion in the
consumer portfolio. during 2009, lending-related commitments decreased by $130.3billion, managed
loans decreased by $112.4billion and derivative receivables decreased by $82.4billion.
while overall portfolio exposure declined, the firm provided more than $600billion in new loans
and lines of credit to consumer and wholesale clients in 2009, including individuals, small
businesses, large corporations, not-for-profit organizations, u.s. states and municipalities, and
other financial institutions.
in the table below, reported loans include loans retained; loans held-for-sale (which are
